k account, so I try and keep my best symbol on all my group at all times, be it a group in Velks or a Raid.  I find that when I'm activally playing ( I just moved and don't have internet until Oct. 26th ) I spend 1.5-2k a week on peridots.  I play almost nightly and find myself raiding about 3 times a week right now.<br><br>So how about you?<br><br> <p>Merkaba54 ClericLanys T'Vyl</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uulaian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ulaian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/10/01 4:27:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paying for Peridots</span><hr size=1> When playing my cleric - usally around 200pp per day after split and money items are factored in. Karnors (where I am grouping currently, haven't bothered to get a seb key yet) doesn't have a hell of a lot of money items <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Ulaian Moonleaf <BR>-Warder <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukayshasoulsinger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaysha Soulsinger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/10/01 4:33:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paying for Peridots</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Edit: When I say I cast Symbol, I mean the Peridot ones. I realise that the Jasper one is a good alternative in some cases, but I hate carrying too many different items ... my inventory is cramped as it is, usually. So when I cast Symbol, it's usually Peridot <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br>It really depends on how fast the MoBs are damaging the people.<br><br>If the situation gets somewhat dangerous, I will Symbol the Enchanter, and more often than not also the Monk and other characters who cannot take dedicated attention from the MoBs for a long time. If it gets really dangerous in that anyone in the party might be at risk of quickly becoming Monster Munch I will symbol my entire party.<br><br>Unfortunately the Symbol lasts just an hour, and takes a full mana bar to cast (well, close to it anyway). <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Edit: I mean when buffing up the entire party with Symbol</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br>If I can simply heal everyone in time with little risk of coming too late, I don't use Symbol.<br><br>On Raids either the Clerics from our guild get money from the guildbank (and then only if it's a guildraid - we're not a rich guild) or pay for them ourselves (with compensation at the end when money items are randomed over the people attending; those who spent money for spells like Symbol or Rune get compensated beforehand). Sure it happens that you don't nearly play even, but it can also happen that you play more than even. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukayshasoulsinger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaysha Soulsinger</A> at: 10/11/01 1:24:04 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubettyaspoon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BettyASpoon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/10/01 6:13:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paying for Peridots</span><hr size=1> I'd pretty much agree with Kaysha.  It really depends on how rough the area is.  I usually end up using Naltron for Main assist/puller and the chanter, with a little Pinzarn for everyone else.  If it's really bad, or a raid, I'll use Naltron for everyone.  If it's pretty safe spot,not at lot of fast damage happening, then Pizarns all around.  Really help cut down the cost if you factor in those Pinzarns.<br><br>For raids, I usually end up going through about 2 stacks of Peridots.  For a normal XP week - maybe one of peridots and two of jaspers.   <p><center><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=31996"><img border="0" src="http://www.neverlore.net/Images/azzmoe.jpg"></a><br><A href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=31996"><font color="#0000ff">Moerne Shadowbone</a><br></font><font color="#0000cc">Handmaiden of Innoruuk<br></font><font color="#000066">Cursed wife of <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=49011"><font color="#000066">Azzlegog Shadowbone</font></a><br></font><a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/bmischief&mayhem"><font color="#000099">Mischief&Mayhem</font></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ufelishannasecretlight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Felishanna Secretlight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cyber Pimp</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/10/01 6:14:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paying for Peridots</span><hr size=1> OOC.<br>Peridots cost a fortune. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Up to 58 it is a nightmare. 58-59 once you have Naltron's Mark is a sweet blessing. 60 is a nightmare again, once you have Aegolism.<br><br>Some are bankrolled by their (big) guilds. Those of us who are not, have to manage as we can. A typical HoT raid alone can cost me 300pp+ in Peridots. I only raid occasionally, I'm not a big time raider, never will be, and even I have outlayed over 1k pp in a week a number of times; I can only imagine what raid-oriented clerics get through. Thankfully, most raid leaders I deal with will try to recompense clerics for the cost, out of any drops, or (if it is primarily a raid for one guild) out of the guilds' raid funds (or in some cases, from their own pockets, I think). If not, I have to finance it myself, and accept this as the way of the world. This is why clerics are mostly poor.<br><br>Xp groups are different, though. If you consistantly find you are not having your costs covered by the same people in an xp group situation, where there are plenty of money items dropping, explain to the group the cost of outlay you are making. If they still ignore this, either don't cast (peridot) symbols, or find kinder folks to group with. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I know when I play Mage, I am the first to say, give all or at least a substantial number of money items to the group cleric.<br> <p>--------------------------------------<BR><BR><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=49771">Felishanna Secretlight</A><BR>High Priestess of Tunare<BR><A HREF="http://pub36.ezboard.com/bheroes795">Heroes of the Old Lands</A><BR>Lanys T'Vyl.<BR><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Action=Journal&Id=49771">[Journal]</A> &#32<A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Action=Journal&Jid=5726&Id=49771">[Roleplay Rules]</A> &#32<A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Action=Journal&Jid=10096&Id=49771">[Trade Skills]</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utanilium.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tanilium</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cyber Pimp</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/10/01 7:03:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paying for Peridots</span><hr size=1> Felish,<br><br>You need to group with Juger and I. We're poor, but as least we have the sense to carry a stack with us. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulaellanna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laellanna</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/10/01 12:34:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/teriyakidonut/laellanna.gif http://members.home.net/teriyakidonut/laellanna.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paying for Peridots</span><hr size=1> Every HoT raid I've been on, I've footed the bill personally for the Peridots (on the average it is around 300-400pp).  It's beginning to get to the point where I'm thinking of not going on open/semi-open raids because the raid leader doesn't consider this at all.  I don't usually mind, but going on 5 straight raids with no help at all hurts a bit (it's not even the pp, it's the fact that we split up and everyone says &quot;great raid&quot;, and ports out).  Heck, on the last raid, I even footed the bill to get a walled corpse summoned.  Paid a few Star Rubies to the necro to summon the corpse so I could rez it.  I do not Aego people who aren't &quot;crucial&quot; to the raid (pullers, MA, SA, debuffers, slowers, CoHer).<br><br>I go through about 1kpp a week in peridots.  Luckily, I have one of the most wonderful groups in all of Lanys (/HUG Expendable, Lelleasha, Zapin, and Brask).  Without them I'd have quit a long time a go, we have a fund which gets all of our equipment, peridots, etc...  We're not all in the same guild, just a group of online friends who play together and trust each other almost implicitly.<br><br>in l33t terms:<br>friends &gt;&gt;&gt; loot<br>friends &gt;&gt;&gt; raids<br>friends &gt;&gt;&gt; EQ<br><br>Odd how the money problems go away when you have a group of friends who are great players and all share the burdens of the game.<br><br>Laellanna/Daena <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulashannavalrynn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lashanna Valrynn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/10/01 5:17:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://students.washington.edu/zip/eq/lashport.jpg  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paying for Peridots</span><hr size=1> When I was doing HoT 2 times a week it was 1k for thoes (combined not each).  It's also one of the reason I don't go often...nothing like paying 5k to loose on 58 drops before your first drop while other get 5-6 drops at no-cost <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    actually that whole time wiped out my bank account and got me a bit bitter at one point.  So I just stoped going and put it all back into perspective and am no longer bitter...just picky about the HoT raid (prefer to go with a lot of friends) and don't do many anymore.  <br><br>Otherwise exping, assuming normal groups and not uber sweet groups who bring gems and pay me full back for gems, it's about 400-500pp a week out of my own pocket after spilt and money items.  Usually about 100pp for hate after money items and  something like 400pp-800pp for fear raids depending on the situation.<br><br>Also I symbol for exping is Me, ench, Main tank and/or puller and any other tanks that are takeing so major dmg to get use of symbol,  on raids it's usually my grouped tanks not on aego and ench, or with no aego (usually means I'm close to the highest is not the highest cleric there) also the ench, MA and/or puller  <p><center><img src="http://students.washington.edu/zip/eq/misch.jpg"></center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulashannavalrynn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lashanna Valrynn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0> at: 10/10/01 5:35:33 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ugalaanisolinari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galaani Solinari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cyber Pimp</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/10/01 11:33:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paying for Peridots</span><hr size=1> Well before Seb, it's kinda hard to afford peridots for each groups... no money items to pay you back, and everyone is quick to forget that 1 symbol = 10 pp...<br><br>After, it's all good and Im agree : main tank / int caster is ok.. <p><IMG SRC =  http://www.brainbubbles.de/sigs/GalArachn.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukateki.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kateki</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/11/01 7:37:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://a1032.g.akamai.net/f/1032/81/30m/www.gamesville.lycos.com/art_gv/ribbon_small.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paying for Peridots</span><hr size=1> Hey all,<br><br>It all depends on the situation. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Most of my peridots are used on raids, and not so much in xp groups.<br><br>I have been in velks the last couple of weeks and rarely do I cast symbol. If I do, it's on the chanter/tank/puller. Most of the time the group is just so strong there is no need. I don't<br>use it on myself at all. This is for xp hunting on spiders.<br><br>If I'm in a tents/pits Kobold group then everyone would get it and I can go through 200pp on a week night easy. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Seb is the same way. But the drops are usally better in these situations and my increased peridot cost is covered np.<br><br>I hardly ever let a group member die when xp hunting. Maybe one a week at most, and that's usally from a train or some freak accident, like ld or lag.<br><br>As a side note, I will keep death pact on the chanter/bard. I have never had a chance to see if it really works though. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>Also, that MoK is a awesome spell and I cast it on all mobs. It really helps keep all the melee members healed.<br><br>Well after all this, I would have to say that symbols and death pacts run me about 500pp a week, 1k for heavy raiding after split and money items are factored in.<br><br><br>Take care all,<br><br>Kateki Cerberuss<br>56 Templar of Vita Infinita<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulittlecherub.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Little Cherub</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/11/01 8:38:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paying for Peridots</span><hr size=1> In exp groups, I suggest asking beforehand if you can be the master looter.  Or if someone else already is talk to them in tells asking if you can be recompensated for your peridots after you're all done grouping and just keep a running tab.  That has usually worked for me, you just have to remind people that the symbols that keep you guys alive aren't free.<br><br>On raids, depending on how busy the raid leader is, I suggest talking to them asking if they can save the plat and money items to help compensate the clerics after.  If they're rude or unwillingly to negotiate something to help the clerics out, don't go on the raid.  Tell other clerics on the raid what the raid leader said, if they have no clerics, they don't have a raid. <p><HR WIDTH="90%" align="center"><TABLE ALIGN="center" BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="1" WIDTH="90%"><TR><TD width="90" align="center"><img src="http://members.aol.com/bel1inda/MiniCherub.gif"></TD><TD><FONT face="Times New Roman" SIZE="+1"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8276">Cherub DwarvenAngel</a> <BR>High Priest of <a href="http://eqvisions.com">Visions</a><BR><small><i>"It's kind of fun to do the impossible."</i></small></font></TD></TR></TABLE><HR WIDTH="90%" align="center"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubordasen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bordasen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/11/01 10:31:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paying for Peridots</span><hr size=1> Honestly, I don't keep track of how much I spend.  It seems like every time I need money, Our guild sends a group or two to Seb for a few hours, and I masterloot.  I split when I remember, but unless someone says something about gems, I usually end up with all gemdrops for the night.  That keeps me in Peridots for a good long time.<br><br>I love casting Aegolism, and it always goes on the tank, the chanter, the shaman, and the necro, along with myself.  The evacer only gets it if asked for.  <br><br>Bordasen<br>High Priest<br>Second Covenant <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulaellanna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laellanna</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/11/01 11:44:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/teriyakidonut/laellanna.gif http://members.home.net/teriyakidonut/laellanna.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paying for Peridots</span><hr size=1> Some of us don't have guild banks Bord <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ... plus, you can always just rent that ho-bard Leo out... I'm sure there are those out there silly enough to pay a mint for his &quot;services&quot;.<br><br>Honestly, I don't think any cleric out there who raids on a semi-regular basis can get by without external help.  If not for my personal group's fund, I'd be flat broke 100% of the time, or compromising by selling gear.  <br><br>Oh... I love Aego too!... nothing like having so many HPs even on the INT caster that you might as well CH instead of CE... lol.<br><br>Laellanna/Daena <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/urasputyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rasputyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/15/01 6:12:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paying for Peridots</span><hr size=1> The way that I like to do it is like Little Cherub said.<br>First off I use both Naltron and Pinzarn (sp??).  Melee all get Naltron and everyone else gets Pinzarn.   I also always have my enchanter hotkeyed for a heal.  Now money items are rare in places like Karnors so I volunteer to ML.  I then ask if anyone minds if I keep the FS to offset Reagent cost.  I tried to keep at least 10 to 12 slots free for FS.  Now that would make me heavier but with a CHA buff would sell for 50 to 60 PP.  That would help quite a bit.  Now of course Seb is better but sometimes small items add up and help cover costs.   It is not to be greedy but I would be very broke without it.<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/urasputyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rasputyn</A> at: 10/15/01 6:14:01 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umathii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mathii</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/17/01 4:23:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paying for Peridots</span><hr size=1> *pokes her head in*<br><br>As a shaman generally I ask not to be symboled in a regular group.  I always have regen and my own HP buffs on me, HB is nice, and unless I or the puller do something stupid I dont need the extra hp.  <br>A shaman should be able to control most of their own aggro, and the only time as a shaman I need extra HP is when I am trying to play crowd control.  Then I can get beat down pretty bad as roots break.  Generally speaking though most of the damage a good shaman takes is self-inflicted, with the occasional smack or 2 from a pissed off slowed mob.  Shamen generally have decent AC and HP and can take a couple smacks without trouble especially since the mobs smacking us are usually 70% slower than before <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br><br>Also, in any group I am in I try to make sure the clerics get their costs back.  I like grouping with clerics and I don't think anyone should leave a group with less cash than they started with.<br><br> <p>Mathi Bear<BR>Luminary<BR><i>"All changes require catalysts."</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubordasen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bordasen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/18/01 10:40:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paying for Peridots</span><hr size=1> You're kind of missing something Mathii.  In another thread, you say that you Cannibilize down to 80% hp.  Well, if I throw Aego on you, you now have an additional 1100 hp.  You can Cannibilize down a lot farther (get more mana) and still be at or above 80% hp.  This is the main reason to Aego Shamans, not because they are getting hit.<br><br>Bordasen<br>High Priest<br>Second Covenant <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umathii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mathii</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/18/01 10:52:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paying for Peridots</span><hr size=1> While having a larger hp pool potentially means having a larger mana pool, over time in groups the only thing that matters is how fast you are getting the mana / hp back.  <br><br>The recovery rate is the limiting factor, not the size of the mana / hp pool.  Raids are different, and a larger hp / mana pool can make a big difference there. <p>Mathi Bear<BR>Luminary<BR><i>"All changes require catalysts."</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulaellanna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laellanna</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/18/01 12:31:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/teriyakidonut/laellanna.gif http://members.home.net/teriyakidonut/laellanna.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paying for Peridots</span><hr size=1> A larger HP pool for everyone is just compensating for mistakes imo.  We all make mistakes on pulls, heals, cc, etc...Aegoing the Shaman means I have a few more seconds to react in the event of any type of accident.  The death of any key party member often means a great deal of lost time (e.g. evac + cr), and when you balance the extra 2 minutes it takes to Aego that person and possibly prevent the lost time, it's worth it in the long run.<br><br>If we were all perfect and everything went according to proper probabilities, I'd bet there one would never need to symbol anyone else.. but alas, we're all human <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Laellanna/Daena <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umathii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mathii</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/18/01 1:14:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paying for Peridots</span><hr size=1> /agree<br><br>Good points <p>Mathi Bear<BR>Luminary<BR><i>"All changes require catalysts."</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udalnareklifeinstater.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DalnarekLifeinstater</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/22/01 1:20:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paying for Peridots</span><hr size=1> Well, one easy way to cut down on the cost of peridots a little (and granted it is just a little) is to request peridots in place of cash for rezzes.  A lot of people carry them around for this expressed purpose and for those of you that dont, a 49+ rez will gladly be traded for 3-5 peridots.  It is cheaper than donating 100pp and the cleric can stay in the field longer with that little bit of influx.  <br>Another way to save money is to get a chanter to get them for you.  They can almost always get a lower proce than the cleric for the gems. <p><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=45014">Dalnarek Lifeinstater</a><br>52 cleric of <a href="http://www.eqbloodsong.com">Bloodsong</a><br>Sardellion McKief20 warrior of  <a href="http://www.eqbloodsong.com">Bloodsong</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udregsorhealsall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dregsor Healsall</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/27/01 12:31:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paying for Peridots</span><hr size=1> I try to keep all members of the party running around with symbol, show and HB at all times.  The added AC and HP make it easier for me to keep everyone alive and usually after a combat or 2 you can tell who does not need the buffs as much and slack on them while healing and refreshing the others in the group.  This strategy can be expensive, like 200-400 per night, but its worth it when you can run some of the nastier camps without a corpse run all night.  Generally, an open group will not turn you down for reimbursement for peridots, and I have been lucky enough to usually have some caring party member mention the cost so I am saved the semi-embarrasing situation of asking for extra loot.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Dregsor Healsall<br>55th level Templar of Rodcet Nife <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showMessageRange?topicID=222.topic&start=21&stop=27>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showMessage?topicID=190.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showMessage?topicID=229.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/bluesparty/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.emailToFriend?topicID=222.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="E